I hope that these current turbulences will replace more calm.
Let us take advantage of the opportunity we have in 2013.
Prime Minister Zapatero seems to have understood this too, and his double statement (reforms promised after a meeting with big last Saturday and yesterday’s announcement of new measures) suggests that, despite the criticism of Merkel, the idea of putting things in order has opened up.
But the red line Germany has drawn is here, and it doesn’t seem to want to move with it.
